    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but those \"small steps\" feel so fake. like putting a bandaid on a gunshot wound. even if we do everything right, the math just doesn't add up. the tipping points are already happening. it feels like fighting a fire with a water pistol. how am i supposed to find meaning in building a life when the foundation is literally crumbling beneath us?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
